{
  "text": "More recent methods [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] follow a 2-step pipeline, consisting of an end-to-end trainable neural network model and a post-processing step that is usually much simpler than previous ones. These methods mainly draw inspiration from techniques in general object detection [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] , [CITATION_7] , [CITATION_8] , and benefit from the highly integrated neural network modules that can predict text instances directly. There are mainly two branches: (1) Anchor-based methods [CITATION_9] , [CITATION_10] , [CITATION_11] , [CITATION_12] that predict the existence of text and regress the location offset only at pre-defined grid points of the input image; (2) Region proposal methods [CITATION_13] , [CITATION_14] , [CITATION_15] , [CITATION_16] , [CITATION_17] , [CITATION_18] that predict and regress on the basis of extracted image region.",
  "correct_citation": {
